The paper deals with the manipulation and simplification of tensor expressions, with a focus on scalar polynomial expressions formed from the Riemann tensor on a four-dimensional metric-compatible manifold. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with symbolic computation, algebraic geometry, computational group theory, and computational physics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SC (Symbolic Computation), cs.GR (Computational Geometry), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CG (Computational Physics).
